2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper proposes a high-order tensorization method named visual data tensorization (VDT) to transform visual data to higher-order forms. This indicates that the paper is related to computer vision and hence, cs.CV is the second most likely sub-category.
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses optimization models and gradient descent methods to optimize the core tensors of tensor-train decomposition. This indicates that the paper is related to algorithms and hence, cs.DS is the third most likely sub-category.
